    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Attractive to All</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jody O'Neil letter holds Matt Wolf's May 14 article on British acting hunks omitted Rupert Everett (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>How in the world does Matt Wolf justify listing 30-plus hot male acting imports [''Britain Sends Out Wave After Wave of Fresh Hunks,'' May 14] without including Rupert Everett? As one who also left Victoria Station for the West Coast and struck gold, Mr. Everett manages to entice men and women alike, from every form of sexual orientation. He also happens to be gay. Is it not possible to be both hunk and homosexual on the same bill?</p>
        <p>JODY O'NEIL  Brooklyn</p>
      </block>
